                                            "title": "<AXValue 0x79393a2e0> {value = error:-25212 type = kAXValueAXErrorType}",
                                            "description": "i’m debugging claude code hooks with tmux for pane focus control.\n\ngoal:\n- when a permission request triggers → visually signal + switch focus to the claude pane (after ~0.5s delay)\n- when the user approves → immediately restore focus back to the previously active pane\n\nsetup:\n- using tmux with multiple panes and multiple windows\n- claude runs in one pane (“claude pane”)\n- user may be in a different pane or even a different window\n\noriginal working config (simplified behavior):\n- PermissionRequest:\n  - save current active pane to /tmp using:\n    tmux list-panes -F '#{pane_active} #{pane_id}' | awk '/^1/{print $2}'\n  - sleep 0.5 (blocking)\n  - tmux select-pane -t $TMUX_PANE  (focus claude pane)\n  - apply red styling\n\n- PostToolUse:\n  - restore focus using:\n    tmux select-pane -t $(cat /tmp/claude_prev_pane_$TMUX_PANE)\n\nproblem:\n- restore feels slow because PostToolUse waits for tool completion\n\nattempted improvement:\n- moved restore logic to PreToolUse to make it instant\n- made PermissionRequest async (removed blocking sleep using tmux run-shell -b)\n\nissues encountered:\n1. async PermissionRequest broke focus switching due to race conditions with claude lifecycle\n2. $TMUX_PANE inside hooks is unreliable (sometimes returns values like \"121\" instead of %pane_id)\n3. tmux commands with \\; caused parsing issues in hooks (JSON → shell → tmux)\n4. tmux select-pane alone does not switch windows → need switch-client when crossing windows\n5. pane targeting ambiguity when using only pane_id in multi-window setups\n6. hooks operate on \"current active pane\" unless explicitly targeted\n7. SessionStart hook caused errors due to $PWD / quoting issues → removed\n8. debugging is hard because hook stderr/stdout is hidden unless using `claude --debug`\n\nkey discoveries:\n- blocking sleep inside PermissionRequest ensures deterministic ordering (no race with claude)\n- async hooks introduce race conditions with claude’s internal focus handling\n- tmux select-pane does NOT switch visible window\n- must use full target (session:window.pane) OR switch-client first\n- file-based state (/tmp) is more reliable than tmux variables in this environment\n- hooks may not run with consistent env vars or client context\n\ncurrent plan:\n- revert to original working config (blocking PermissionRequest + PostToolUse restore)\n- confirm baseline behavior works reliably\n- then migrate restore from PostToolUse → PreToolUse WITHOUT breaking focus switching\n- keep PermissionRequest synchronous to avoid race conditions\n\nopen questions:\n- best way to reliably target claude pane (without relying on $TMUX_PANE)\n- whether PreToolUse restore needs slight delay to avoid claude overriding focus\n- whether switch-client is required for multi-window setups\n- how to robustly handle pane targeting across tmux windows",
